Package com.cafean.CalcServer

Class BlockFileAccessManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • com.cafean.CalcServer.BlockFileAccessManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    public class BlockFileAccessManager
extends java.lang.Thread
    The BlockFileAccessManager is used as part of a system to remotely view possibly very large text files over a possibly very limited network connection. The BFAM also provides access to particular indexed line numbers referred to as Points of Interest.
    Note: Destroy Should be called when BFAM is no longer needed.

        Gets the line number of the first occurrence of inString in the file starting from line startLine; The direction of the search is defined by the boolean forward parameter.
        Parameters:
        inString - the pattern to search the current file for
        startLine - the line to begin searching on
        forward - TRUE if the search should advance the text forward.
        Returns:
        the line number of the first occurrence of the pattern or -1 on error, or -2 while indexing
